### 10. Security Strategy

| Threat | Mitigation |
|--------|-----------|
| **MongoDB Injection** | `express-mongo-sanitize` (already active globally), Mongoose schema validation, type casting |
| **XSS / HTML Injection** | `express-validator` `.escape()` on all string inputs, EJS auto-escaping (`<%= %>`), CSP headers via Helmet |
| **Script Injection** | CSP `script-src: 'self'`, no inline scripts, no `eval()`, no `innerHTML` with user data |
| **NoSQL Injection** | Whitelist-based query construction (never pass raw user input to `$where`, `$gt`, etc.), schema-level type enforcement |
| **CSRF** | Origin/Referer checking for public APIs, existing CSRF tokens for admin |
| **Price Manipulation** | All prices recalculated server-side from DB before order creation |
| **Promo Code Abuse** | Server-side validation only, atomic usage counter, rate limiting |
| **File Upload Attacks** | MIME type validation, file size limits, extension whitelist, storage outside web root consideration |
| **Route Traversal** | Strict prefix isolation (`/order/*`, `/api/public/*` vs `/admin/*`, `/dashboard/*`) |
| **Brute Force** | Rate limiting on all public endpoints |

